"{\n  \"text\": \"I've been documenting my cucumber project and this year we lost the season early. It looks like uh August weather came in June, and so it got very hot and very dry, and even though I was watering the plants daily, uh you just can't keep up with it. And uh even though they were living and they're still living, uh we kind of came to the end of the season, and I put up a shade cloth trying to extend it a little bit, and I'm not completely sure I can if the rains come back a little bit and see I put up those little bars or those little uh wooden braces. There's the shade cloth. I'm gonna extend it over the whole thing like there. And uh as I go in there, you can see it's really nicely shaded, a little bit cooler. But you can see what's happened right here. There's the devastation. There's where I've lost all the foliage, right going climbing up. On top, it's still good, but we'll lose a bunch of that here in the next couple days as it gets super hot. And this was the tally, this is what we got out of it. About $1,500 worth of cucumber sales. Uh, this is some of the cucumber kimchi I made, and it was delicious. It's my favorite. And these are the farmers markets you'll find me at. Hey, thanks y'all. I appreciate it.\",\n  \"sentences\": [\n    {\n      \"text\": \" I've been documenting my cucumber project and this year we lost the season early.\",\n      \"start\": 0.16,\n      \"end\": 5.12,\n      \"duration\": 4.96,\n      \"confidence\": 0.998,\n      \"tokens\": [\n        {\n          \"text\": \" I\",\n          \"start\": 0.16,\n          \"end\": 0.32,\n          \"duration\": 0.16,\n          \"confidence\": 0.997\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"'\",\n          \"start\": 0.32,\n          \"end\": 0.4,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 0.999\n        },\n        {\n          \"text\": \"ve\",\n          \"start\": 0.4,\n          \"end\": 0.48,\n          \"duration\": 0.08,\n          \"confidence\": 1.0